					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13332407#post-4654887</guid>
				<title>Re: -1</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13332407/scp-5915#post-4654887</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 20 May 2020 09:30:52 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>RockTeethMothEyes</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4022320</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>The Katrina subplot isn't even necessary for the story to work</p> </blockquote> <p>While I understand that this part of the article may comes off as distasteful and that I certainly don't mean any disrespect, this section of the article effectively makes up half of the content. Without it, it's very much just a strange phenomenon that happens. I could use a different hurricane, sure, but that may also irk at people that disagree with the general use of disasters, regardless of name. I'd be interested to hear what you might suggest to improve on this, since out of four reviewers, seven comments, and several users having read and voted, this is the only comment to have mentioned distaste in this particular aspect of the story.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13332407#post-4654791</guid>
				<title>-1</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13332407/scp-5915#post-4654791</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 20 May 2020 07:49:22 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Dr Whattman</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3108559</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>&quot;by means of lifting and dropping their heads onto sharp rocks&quot;</p> <p>The Katrina stuff like this comes off as very distasteful, and the reason I believe most writers don't use real world tragedies in their skips. This may just be a case of something hitting too close to home since I'm from the Gulf South, but the imagery and phrases like the one above really, really rub me the wrong way. The Katrina subplot isn't even necessary for the story to work, and I'm sorry but it feels absolutely gross reading that. -1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
